Wolfblade::

She smiled and stopped tickling. "OK, I won't do that again. Well, how
about, for a while. A short while. On second thought, I'll just get
you later on, when you least expect it." she said with a slightly evil
grin. She knew it was rather a one sided tickle fight. And her honor
wouldn't let her do it for long. But as a femme and having fun with a
bot that she felt was her spark mate, it was ok to do it once in a while.

She looked upward towards the forests. "I wonder how close we are?"
Still holding his hands, she nudged her arm scanner with her other
hand, still in his grasp, and checked the screen. "Hmm, just two
clicks south, and we're there."  She smiled up at him and kissed his
cheek. "See? We're at the edge of the forest now, and soon we'll be at
our target zone."  She put the scanner away and smiled lovingly at
him. She leaned up and kissed him again.
